text.tspan: Energy intensity level of primary energy is the ratio between energy supply and gross domestic product measured
at purchasing power parity. Energy intensity is an indication of how much energy is used to produce one unit of
economic output. Lower ratio indicates that less energy is used to produce one unit of output.
Source: World Bank, Sustainable Energy for All (SE4ALL)
